Perl 6 also has <i>dynamic scoping</i>.  But I don't think they kept it just for backward compatibility with Perl 4 & 5 :)<p>Here is another example where <i>dynamic scoping</i> can indeed be very useful:<p><pre><code>    sub bar { 'bar' }
    sub baz { bar() }

    sub foo {
        no warnings 'redefine';
        local *bar = sub { 'My Bar' };
        baz();
    }

    say foo();   # => 'My Bar'
    say baz();   # => 'bar'</code></pre>
